{
  "stem": "15768.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My grandmother was taken on a stretcher to Theresienstadt and perished there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My young cousin, that I spent all my growing up years with, was deported and also was lost in the camp.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so I always felt a very strong obligation to their memory, to carry on Jewish faith, which I do to this day.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so when my mother's-- in the family, my mother's family, there really wasn't all that much emphasis on religion, and I always had terrible arguments with my father who persistently said there is no God.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I said I want to go to synagogue, and he said you go do what you want.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I think you're foolish.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he did this until even when I was an adult and I had children later.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He nixed it all the way, and I fought him all the way, and said, no, it's not true, because look-- and I trotted out all these things.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And He never spoke about his experience in Buchenwald, but I knew that that was the reason why he had turned away from God.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Not his religion, but God.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And so now, we're in New York City.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We're in Washington Heights where a lot of the refugees-- in fact, for a while there it was dubbed Little Germany, only the Jewish kind, up at 178th Street in New York City.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And again, I started school, and at that school, one of the first things that I remember is I learned my multiplication tables and my addition in German.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And to this day in my head, when I do-- when I do multiplication and adding a column of numbers, I do it in German.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
